   <div id="main">
    <div class="column page--front" id="content" role="main">
     <div id="homepage-content">
      <p style="text-align: justify;">
       The
       <strong>
        National Institute for Transportation and Communities (NITC)
       </strong>
       , one of five U.S. Department of Transportation national university transportation centers, is a program of the
       <a href="http://trec.pdx.edu/">
        Transportation Research and Education Center
       </a>
       (TREC) at Portland State University.
       <br/>
       <br/>
       The NITC program is a
       <a href="http://www.pdx.edu" target="_blank">
        Portland State
       </a>
       -led partnership with the
       <a href="http://uoregon.edu/" target="_blank">
        University of Oregon
       </a>
       ,
       <a href="http://www.oit.edu" target="_blank">
        Oregon Institute of Technolog
       </a>
       y,
       <a href="http://www.utah.edu" target="_blank">
        University of Utah
       </a>
       and new partners
       <a href="https://uanews.arizona.edu/story/ua-part-15m-federal-grant-national-center-designation" target="_blank">
        University of Arizona
       </a>
       and
       <a href="http://www.uta.edu/news/releases/2016/12/DOT-UTC-transportation-grants.php" target="_blank">
        University of Texas at Arlington
       </a>
       . We pursue our theme — improving mobility of people and goods to build strong communities — through research, education and technology transfer.
       <br/>
       <br/>
      </p>
      <p>
       <img src="http://nitc.trec.pdx.edu/sites/default/files/nitc_4c_horiz_tag_450.png" style="vertical-align: middle; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" width="300"/>
      </p>
      <p>
       <img alt="NITC Partner University Logos" src="http://nitc.trec.pdx.edu/sites/default/files/University%20Partner%20Logos%20-%20NITC%20Webinar%20Footer_transparent.png" style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" width="850"/>
      </p>
     </div>
    </div>
